					<head>Ḥidushim</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>Contains Novellae on the tractate Ḳidushin.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="tmr-Hebr">Hebrew, Aramaic</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="89v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ḥidushim </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">חדושים</title>
							<note>
								<p>The work might have been written by a contemporary of Nahmanides. The work quotes several rabbinic authorities, including Shelomoh ben Aderet, Shimshon of Sens, Alfasi, Yitsḥaḳ Abba Mari and Maimonides.</p>
								<p>Of the novellae on the last chapter, only a small portion has been copied.</p>
								<p>Folio 1, which is vellum, and belongs to the 12th or 13th century, contains a fragment of a tractate Berakhot (part of folio 34 in the printed editions).</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>89 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>205</height>
										<width>140</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>170/185</height>
										<width>115/120</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>89 folios (+ 3 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and  at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 5 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Some of the quires are incomplete.</p>
									<p>Partly worm-eaten.</p>
									<p>Stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="20 32" writtenLines="2032">
									<p>Catchwords on every verso, partially cut away.</p>
									<p>Chapter titles given in larger characters.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Oriental semi-cursive script of the 15th century, badly written in parts.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folios 2r and 98v contain doodles.</p>
							<p>Folios 1r-1v belong to a different manuscript (vellum). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yehudah Ha-Kohen Ashkenazi</name>: inscribed, folio 1r, 3r. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Shemu᾿el Casani</name> (?): inscribed in a note of sale, folio 1r. </p>
						</additions>
